kze-u7n4-fr5b,"Dear Comptroller Hsu,  Thank you, Comptroller Hsu, for taking up the issue of climate change and banks.  I am writing to you because I lost my childhood home to Hurricane Charley in 2004 so I've seen firsthand the devastation that natural disasters can have on communities.  Even as banks publicly claim to be taking climate change seriously and phasing out financing for greenhouse gas emissions, they are investing billions into companies that produce fossil fuels. Banks‚Äô continued investments in fossil fuels are driving climate change ‚Äì a crisis that puts our financial system, people of color and low-income communities, and our planet at risk. Regulators must not let financial institutions gamble with our future. We need you to push banks to take the urgent steps necessary to address the dangers they face from climate change, and stop their short-term business decisions from endangering our economy and communities.
