I support the proposed guidance‚Äôs recommendations to banks that they:
1. Incorporate climate-related risk management into every level of business, including phasing out investment in the world‚Äôs vast stock of carbon-intensive assets and ramping up investment in retrofitting  or replacing these assets with low or zero emission alternatives;
2. Plan for climate change over a long time horizon, and update models as additional data becomes available; and
3. Develop clear definitions of possible climate-related risk exposures, and metrics for setting limits; 
