kzk-0zfp-or04,"Thank you, Comptroller Hsu, for taking up the issue of climate change and banks.  I am asking you to use the full extent of your authority to stop banks from continuing to pour billions of dollars into continuing and expanding fossil fuel production.  Many of these banks declare their commitment to stop funding the climate crisis, but in fact refuse to phase out their financing of greenhouse gas emissions at anything like the rate necessary to avert utter disaster.  We simply cannot afford their prioritization of short-term profit over the long-term devastation we face: rising oceans, violent storms, unprecedented droughts and rapidly increasing desertification, uncontrollable wildfires, and global loss of biodiversity.  Regulators must require banks to reduce these risks by committing to and carrying out real change. They must: 
