l24-vcdh-dnq2,"To: Public Comment File    From: Joanne Phillips, Counsel, Chief Counsel‚Äôs Office     Date: March 28, 2022    Subject: Meeting with RMI‚Äôs Center for Climate-Aligned Finance on March 23rd, 2022        On March 23rd, 2022, representatives from the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency  (OCC) met with representatives from RMI‚Äôs Center for Climate-Aligned Finance (CCAF)  regarding the OCC‚Äôs draft Principles for Climate-Related Financial Risk Management for  Large Banks (draft Principles). CCAF representatives discussed their views of the proposed  draft Principles and expressed broad support for the draft Principles.     OCC Attendees  Darrin Benhart, Climate Change Risk Officer  Jonathan Fink, Assistant Chief Counsel  Joanne Phillips, Counsel, Chief Counsel‚Äôs Office     CCAF Attendees   Alexander Murray, Associate with RMI‚Äôs Center for Climate-Aligned Finance  Whitney Mann, Senior Associate with the Climate Aligned Industries team of RMI‚Äôs Center  for Climate-Aligned Finance","On March 23, 2022, representatives from the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC) met with RMI‚Äôs Center for Climate-Aligned Finance (CCAF) to discuss the OCC‚Äôs draft Principles for Climate-Related Financial Risk Management for Large Banks. The CCAF expressed broad support for the draft Principles. The meeting included OCC attendees such as Darrin Benhart, Climate Change Risk Officer, and Jonathan Fink, Assistant Chief Counsel, as well as CCAF attendees like Alexander Murray, Associate, and Whitney Mann, Senior Associate with the Climate Aligned Industries team."
l24-vdmb-0rs6,"To: Public Comment File    From: Joanne Phillips, Counsel, Chief Counsel‚Äôs Office     Date: April 11, 2022    Subject: Meeting with the Financial Services Forum on March 30th, 2022        On March 30th, 2022, representatives from the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency  (OCC) met with representatives and constituents from the Financial Services Forum (FSF)  regarding the OCC‚Äôs draft Principles for Climate-Related Financial Risk Management for  Large Banks (draft Principles). FSF representatives discussed their views on the proposed  draft Principles. These views included the need for flexibility and support for the use of  scenario analysis rather than stress testing.     OCC Attendees  Darrin Benhart, Climate Change Risk Officer  David Bates, Director for Commercial Credit Risk   Julie Blake, Director, Banking Relations  Ryan Portell, Program Manager, Outreach  Joanne Phillips, Counsel, Chief Counsel‚Äôs Office     FSF Attendees  Priya Bindra  Ahmed Elcott  Jillian Pasco  Jeeyoung Choi  Kristin Solheim  Andrene Smith  Raymond Conover  Timothy Becker  Clare Davies  Linda French  Steven Patterson  Ciara Horigan  Lavon Von Redden  Ken Connolly  Amanda Sondey  Cathy Ansell    2  Aileen Long  Kevin Fromer   Brett Quick  Sean Campbell  Tiffany Haas   Megan Guiltinan   Barbara Hagenbaugh","On March 30, 2022, the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC) met with the Financial Services Forum (FSF) to discuss the OCC's draft Principles for Climate-Related Financial Risk Management for Large Banks. FSF representatives expressed their views, emphasizing the need for flexibility in the implementation of these principles. They advocated for the use of scenario analysis over stress testing as a preferred method for assessing climate-related financial risks. The meeting included various representatives from both the OCC and FSF, highlighting the collaborative effort to address climate-related financial risks in the banking sector."
